50|$|Skid marks {{will vary}} {{depending}} on whether the car uses ABS or not. If not, there will be two lines. The darker marks on the outside are from the front wheels, while the back tires leave thinner marks. This is because the force exerted on them makes the wheels take on a conical shape. If the car uses ABS, the marks will be much fainter as less heat is produced by the <b>release-stop</b> mechanism of ABS. Scuff marks may be visible however with ABS.|$|E

